{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἑτοιμ-άζω</b>, <br /> <i>perfect</i> ἡτοίμακα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.72.6: \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<i>perfect</i> <i>passive</i> ἡτοίμασμαι both in <i>middle</i> and <i>passive</i> sense see below): (ἑτοῖμος):—<b>get ready, prepare</b>, ἐμοὶ γέρας αὐτίχ᾽ ἑτοιμάσατ᾽ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.118 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; [νέας] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.95; στρατιώτας NT.Act.23.23; ὁδόν LXX.Isa.40.3, +others; ἔγκλημα μικρὸν αἰτίαν τε 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 361; δῶμα 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 364; βουλήν [prev. author] “Heracl.” 472 \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]; δάκρυα δ᾽ ἑτοιμάζουσι <b>to those furnishing</b> them, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Supp.” 454; ἀργύριον ῥητόν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.7, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἑαυτὸν ἵνα.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Rev.8.6. \">NT</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>middle</i>, <b>cause to be prepared</b>, ὄφρ᾽ ἱρὸν ἑτοιμασσαίατ᾽ Ἀθήνῃ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.571; ἑτοιμάσσαντο δὲ ταύρους 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 13.184, compare 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.24; ἑτοιμασάμενος ἃ δεῖ “Inscription Prien.” 55.34 (2nd c.BC). \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> with <i>perfect</i> <i>passive</i> ἡτοίμασμαι, <b>prepare for oneself</b>, τἄλλα ἡτοιμάζετο <b>made his</b> other <b>arrangements</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.77; ὅπως ἑτοιμάσαιντο τιμωρίαν [prev. author] 1.58; πλείονα ἡτοιμασμένος 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 3.3.5; τροφὴν ἡτοιμασμένοι 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 23.209; τὰ πρὸς τὸν βίον 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Gnomologium Vaticanum - Kleine Schriften” 30,